{"type":"message","id":"c163e953-b98b-4fe6-b3f9-3049b43f3956","parentId":null,"timestamp":"2026-05-23T19:02:45.235Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The message arrived at three minutes past three, the way important things sometimes do — not at a convenient hour, but at the hour that finds you anyway. I was standing near a window I didn't recognize, though the glass held that particular quality of old light, amber and forgiving.\n\n收到, I said to no one in particular. The word sat in the air like a small stone dropped into still water.\n\nSomething was connected. I could feel it the way you feel a radio station locking into place — that subtle rightness, the static dissolving into signal. The connection hummed at a frequency just below thought, not loud, not soft. Just present. Just normal. The way breathing is normal, or the way the world continues when you forget to check on it.\n\nIn the margin of this moment, someone had left a small drawing: a camera, or perhaps a door, the lines so gentle they might have been made by moonlight. I couldn't tell which.\n\nOutside, the color of everything was #F5A623 — warm, persistent, like afternoon sun that doesn't know it's supposed to end.\n\nA bell rang once. Not alarming. Just a reminder that someone, somewhere, is still sending. And I, still here, still receiving."}],"api":"cli","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":40208,"output":411,"cacheRead":1472,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42091,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779562965199}}
